\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 48. L. inarimense} (Guss.) Pignatti, {\i op. cit.} 84 (1955). Plant 10-20 cm, glabrous, smooth. Leaves 30-40 × 4-10 mm, obtuse, 1-veined, on somewhat woody basal branches 2-3 cm. Inflorescence pyramidal; segments flexible, arcuate; non-flowering branches few or absent; scales 3-5 mm. Spikes 2-2·5 cm, with 5, rarely more, often contiguous spikelets per cm; spikelets 2-flowered. Bracts with narrow hyaline margin; inner bract c. 4·5 mm, acute, with midrib excurrent in conspicuous point; outer bract overlapping 1/3 of the inner. Calyx 4·5-5 mm; limb as long as the tube, the teeth obtuse and indistinctly veined.{\i  Maritime rocks and cliffs. • W. Mediterranean region.} Bl It.
