\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 49. L. tenoreanum} (Guss.) Pignatti, {\i Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  64:} 365 (1971) ({\i Statice tenoreana} Guss.). Plant glabrous, smooth. Leaves 25-40 × 4-7 mm, lanceolate-spathulate, obtuse, revolute, 1-veined, on woody basal branches 4-8 cm. Inflorescence 10-15 cm, dense, sparingly branched only in the upper half; non-flowering branches absent; scales 1·5-2·5 mm. Spikes 0·9-1·3 cm, with 10-13 contiguous spikelets per cm; spikelets 2-flowered. Inner bract 3·5-4 mm; outer bract overlapping 1/3-1/2 of the inner. Calyx 5-5·5 mm; limb as long as the tube. Corolla c. 6·5 mm.{\i  Calcareous cliffs. • S.W. Italy} ({\i near Castellammare}). It.
