\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 50. L. laetum} (Nyman) Pignatti, {\i loc. cit.} (1971) ({\i Statice duriuscula }subsp.{\i  laeta} Nyman,{\i  S. laeta} Moris, non Salisb.). Plant 10-20 cm, glabrous, slightly rough. Leaves 20-25 × 2-3 mm, linear-spathulate, acute, 1-veined, on woody basal branches 3(-8) cm. Inflorescence dense, branched only in the upper half; non-flowering branches absent. Spikes 1-1·5 cm, with 8 contiguous spikelets per cm; spikelets 2-flowered. Inner bract c. 4·5 mm; outer bract overlapping 1/4-1/3 of the inner. Calyx c. 4 mm; limb 1/2 as long as the tube. Corolla c. 6 mm. • {\i  Coast of W. Sardegna.} Sa.
